  "number": 5222,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/5222",
  "title": "Large bundle size with ES module",
  "body": "### 🐛 Current behavior\r\n\r\nI have just created a new Svelte project using Vite.\r\n\r\nCreated a super simple page without any templating and no added widgets.\r\n\r\nThre result is a large bundle size that includes alot of unused packages.\r\n![main_full (2)](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7306904/208679088-8d7469ab-8d35-4d70-a77a-45998a46d70b.png)\r\n\r\nSome examples of unused code (maybe?):\r\n- Hogan.js\r\n- @algolia/events\r\n- all connectors in the picture\r\n- all components in the picture\r\n\r\nSee this for rollup: https://codesandbox.io/s/dawn-waterfall-sbvly9?file=/index.html\r\n\r\nI think the reason for this is because of inproper imports. Examples:\r\n- https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/blob/master/packages/instantsearch.js/src/lib/InstantSearch.ts#L2\r\n- https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/blob/master/packages/instantsearch.js/src/lib/InstantSearch.ts#L3\r\n\r\n\r\n### 🔍 Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ npm init vite\r\n$ cd new-vite-project\r\n$ yarn add algoliasearch instantsearch.js\r\n```\r\n\r\ninit instantsearch without adding any widgets\r\n```\r\n<script lang=\"ts\">\r\n  import algoliasearch from \"algoliasearch/lite\";\r\n  import instantsearch from \"instantsearch.js/es\";\r\n  const searchClient = algoliasearch('APP_ID', 'APP_KEY');\r\n  const search = instantsearch({\r\n    indexName: 'INDEX',\r\n    searchClient,\r\n  });\r\n  search.start();\r\n\r\n</script>\r\n\r\n<main>\r\n    <p>EMPTY PAGE</p>\r\n</main>\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Live reproduction\r\n\r\nhttps://codesandbox.io/s/dawn-waterfall-sbvly9?file=/index.html\r\n\r\n### 💭 Expected behavior\r\n\r\nHogan.js should not be bundled and the same with unused connectors, widgets and templates.\r\n\r\n### Package version\r\n\r\nalgoliasearch 4.14.3, instantsearch.js 4.49.2, vite 4.0.0, svelte 3.54.0\r\n\r\n### Operating system\r\n\r\nUbuntu\r\n\r\n### Browser\r\n\r\nChrome\r\n\r\n### Code of Conduct\r\n\r\n- [X] I agree to follow this project's Code of Conduct",
